			<h4><a href="#" name="About">What is OPAR?</a></h4>
			<p>
				OPAR is an archive of packages that extend the <a href="http://www.otrs.org">OTRS</a> software.
			</p>
			<p>
				Using OTRS' smart packaging tool, OPM - OTRS package manager, extensions can be built by any 
				developer, packaged and passed on to other users. Through packaging of own changes to the 
				system, the system is then more audit proof. Additionally, the package system backs up all 
				files changed, to make sure that an uninstall is successful.
			</p>

                        <h4><a href="#" name="InstallOPM">Install/Upgrade OPM files</a></h4>
                        <p>
                                You can install the OPM files via OTRS package manager. You can create your own repository
                                and add this repository in SysConfig.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Create a repository at <a href="/repo"><%= __HOST__ %>/repo</a></li>
                                    <li>Complete settings for your repository</li>
                                    <li>Add repo in SysConfig (Framework &rarr; Core::Package &rarr; Package::RepositoryList</li>
                                    <li>Go to package manager and install/upgrade add ons</li>
                                </ol>
                        </p>
